   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>From your Package Savings Program, go to Qualifications and Benefits tab.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Add products to your package. By, default, the package type is Primary. Refer to <xref href="../adding-products_102432695_102432695/102432695_1.xml"
                     format="dita">Adding Products</xref> for more details.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click Save.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To add a product as secondary, under the Products in Bundle tab, click <uicontrol>Add Secondary Product</uicontrol> from the more menu.  A copy of the primary package is created with Package Type as Secondary. </p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="603"
                         href="../attachments/102432721/102432726.png"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter the unit price.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>The bundle price is auto-calculated to reflect all the changes.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click Save.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <div>
         <p>You can also add a product as a secondary product directly from the Product Catalog. When adding a product from the product catalog, set Package Type as Secondary Package and save.</p>
      </div>
